= form_for(@project) do |f|

  .field.reference-number-field
    = f.text_field :reference_num, placeholder: "Project Reference No."
  .col-1.col-5.location
    Project Location
    .address.col-3
      .col-1.address-field
        = f.label :street_address, "Street Address"
        = f.text_field :street_addy, value: current_user.address
      .col-1.address-field
        = f.label :city
        = f.text_field :city, value: current_user.city
    .address.col-2
      .col-1.address-field
        = f.label :state
        = f.text_field :state, value: current_user.state
      .col-1.address-field
        = f.label :zip
        = f.text_field :zip, value: current_user.zip
      .col-1.address-field
        = f.label :country
        = f.text_field :country, value: current_user.country
  .col-2.project-form
    .field.col-1.description-field
      = f.text_area :description, placeholder: "Description of project..."

  %div.card-title
    Mass RFQ
  %table.table.table-bordered.table-striped
    %thead
      %tr
        %th 
          1) 
        %th
          Please fill out #{link_to " this template", Document.find_by(name: "Bid Aero Parts Req Template").attachment_url}. Do NOT change the headers. *
      %tr
        %th 
          2)
        %th
          Once, the file is ready click select File > Save As... And choose File Format: Comma Separated Values (.csv). You must upload a .csv file in order to generate your RFQs.
      %tr
        %th
          3)
        %th
          Upload the file below.
  %br
  %div{style: "font-size: 14px; font-style: italic;"}
    *If you do not have the information for one of the columns, you may leave that column blank. It is important that the headers have the same name as those of our templates, and that no additional columns are used.
  .col-1.container.left-align.part-req-sheet
    = f.file_field :attachment, :accept => 'text/csv'
  .actions.col-1.center-align.project-submit
    %div.submit-btn
      = f.submit "Create Project", class: 'custom-btn btn'